##Special report. | The rescuers are gone

Hey, guys

Function description, here is the "First Finance" magazine (predecessor "first finance weekly") readers club, we discover wonderful business value for you, also invited you to explore the bright business world.

Intern reporter | Yuan Ying

Editor | Xu Shiyu

The epidemic has brought home to people the value of medical resources. To protect medical personnel and people in the field of medical technology is to protect the lives of others. However, the occupational specificity of health workers also means that they are at higher risk of infection.

On the afternoon of February 14, at the State Council's Joint Prevention and Control Mechanism press conference on the epidemic of pneumonia, Zeng Yixin, deputy director of the National Health Commission, said that as of 2400 hours on February 11,1,716 cases of new pneumonia had been confirmed by medical personnel across the country, this accounted for 3.8 per cent of the country's confirmed cases, six of which unfortunately died, or 0.4 per cent of the country's total deaths.

Not only health care workers, but many others are on the front lines in the fight against the epidemic. Take he hui, a 55 year old from Wuhan. After the outbreak, He Hui, a native of Wuhan, volunteered to take part in a volunteer convoy of medical staff, who volunteered to pick up and drop off medical staff. According to He Hui's family, he hui joined the Wuhan volunteer team around New Year's Eve. He stopped his volunteer work after he became unwell. Around January 30, He Hui presented with cough, fever and other symptoms. He was later admitted to Tongji Hospital, affiliated to Tongji Medical College. The result was Shuangyang District. He was transferred to Tongji Hospital in Zhongfa Xincheng district on the evening of February 2. At 1600 hours on February 3, He Hui died in the Zhongfa Xincheng District of Wuhan Tongji Hospital because of invalid treatment.

In this epidemic, all the dead deserve to be remembered. We are here to pay tribute to the health care workers and medical scholars who lost their lives in this epidemic.

Liang Wudong, 62

Former chief physician of Department of Otorhinolaryngology, Xinhua Hospital, Hubei Province Integrated Traditional Chinese and Western medicine hospital

Liang Wudong, 62

Former chief physician of Department of Otorhinolaryngology, Xinhua Hospital, Hubei Province Integrated Traditional Chinese and Western medicine hospital

Liang Wudong specializes in micro-ear neurosurgery, nasal endoscopic minimally invasive surgery, snoring, pediatric Otorhinolaryngology, Voice Diseases of internal and external medicine. The Functional Operation Technique of snoring laryngeal carcinoma is exquisite, and the treatment method of Secretory otitis media is unique.

On January 16, Liang was suspected to have contracted COVID-19 pneumonia. On January 18, he was transferred to Jinyintan Hospital. Liang Wudong died around 7:00 am on January 25,2020.

Li Wenliang, 34

Wuhan Central Hospital ophthalmologist, first-line Doctors Fighting COVID-19 pneumonia, as early as December 30,2019 to the outside world issued a protective alert, known as the "whistle blower. ".

Li Wenliang, 34

Wuhan Central Hospital ophthalmologist, first-line Doctors Fighting COVID-19 pneumonia, as early as December 30,2019 to the outside world issued a protective alert, known as the "whistle blower. ".

Li Wenliang graduated from the Wuhan University in 2011. He holds a doctor of medicine and is a member of the Hubei Ophthalmology Association. He has participated in scientific research projects of the National Natural Science Foundation of China and the Wuhan University, and has been engaged in clinical work in ophthalmology for many years, good at Fundus disease, cataract, Glaucoma diagnosis and treatment. He is currently working in the Ophthalmology Department of the Wuhan Central Hospital. He has published many papers with high level of SCI, and he has made accurate diagnosis and treatment of common eye diseases, especially difficult ones. He sits for consultation every Saturday and Sunday.

On January 8, he contracted COVID-19 pneumonia after receiving a female patient without special protection. Li developed cough on January 10, developed fever on January 11, was hospitalized on January 12, and was transferred to the intensive-care unit on January 14 due to an aggravated condition. He was treated with antibiotics, hormones, antiviral drugs and high flow oxygen inhalation. On February 1, Li Wenliang was diagnosed as a new case of coronary pneumonia.

At around 9:00 p.m. on February 6, some media released the news that Li Wenliang had died. At the same time, there was also news that Li Wenliang was being rescued by ECMO. At 0:38 p.m. on the 7th, an official of Wuhan Central Hospital released a message saying, dr. Li Wenliang "is critically ill and is doing all he can to save him. ".

Li Wenliang died at Wuhan Central Hospital at 2:58 a.m. on Feb. 7, according to official sources.

Hong Ling, 53

Professor, professor, distinguished professor, Huazhong University of Science and Technology, member of Nanooncology Society, China Anti-cancer Association, National Coordinator of Rare Diseases Research Union.

Hong Ling, 53

Professor, professor, distinguished professor, Huazhong University of Science and Technology, member of Nanooncology Society, China Anti-cancer Association, National Coordinator of Rare Diseases Research Union.

In 2007, she accepted an offer from the Huazhong University of Science and Technology to become a professor at the professor, where she modeled her life on model animals, fruit flies and human cells, to study the gene and protein regulatory mechanisms and regulatory networks of major human diseases such as tumors and cardiovascular diseases, and to study the molecular mechanisms of the gene UBIAD1 associated with major human diseases and rare diseases, has made a significant contribution to this field of study.

Professor Hong Ling died at Union Hospital at 2300 hours on February 7,2020 due to ineffectual treatment of new crown pneumonia.

Lin Zhengbin, 63

Renowned Chinese transplant specialist and former deputy chief physician of Tongji Hospital affiliated to Tongji Medical College

Lin Zhengbin, 63

Renowned Chinese transplant specialist and former deputy chief physician of Tongji Hospital affiliated to Tongji Medical College

Lin received his bachelor's degree in clinical medicine in 1983. After graduation, he has been working in the Organ Transplantation Research Institute of Tongji Hospital. He studied at Kanazawa Medical University in Japan and retired in July 2017. He served as deputy director of Organ Transplantation Branch of Wuhan Medical Association. Lin Zhengbin has been engaged in organ transplantation for nearly 40 years. He has made remarkable achievements in kidney transplantation, post-operation management and treatment of critical patients.

According to the Southern Metropolis Daily, Lin was still working before he was infected. He was still being treated at home under isolation until January 24. He was hospitalized only after his condition did not improve. It is not known exactly when and how he was infected, his family is also being treated for new crown pneumonia.

At 11:00 on February 10, Lin Zhengbin passed away via Tongji Hospital, affiliated to Tongji Medical College.

Xu Defu, 62

Chief physician of traditional Chinese medicine, adjunct professor and well-known doctor of Chinese medicine in Ezhou, Research Fellow of the Medical Research Center of Beijing University of Chinese Medicine, standing member of the special committee of Spleen and stomach diseases of the Hubei Society of Traditional Chinese Medicine, and Executive Director of the Chinese Medicine Society of Ezhou.

Xu Defu, 62

Chief physician of traditional Chinese medicine, adjunct professor and well-known doctor of Chinese medicine in Ezhou, Research Fellow of the Medical Research Center of Beijing University of Chinese Medicine, standing member of the special committee of Spleen and stomach diseases of the Hubei Society of Traditional Chinese Medicine, and Executive Director of the Chinese Medicine Society of Ezhou.

In the long-term clinical practice, he gradually groped for a set of clinical experience, formed his own medical characteristics, clinical drug use is flexible, with incorruptibility, simplicity, convenience, experience, on the diagnosis and treatment of difficult diseases quite experience, especially the diagnosis and treatment of liver, gallbladder, spleen and stomach disease is unique, the treatment of stomach disease, digestive tract, diabetes and other diseases is also rich in experience. Published more than 50 academic papers, published "the unreasonable combination of Chinese and Western medicine 150 cases" , "integrated Chinese and Western medicine treatment of common tumors, " and other monographs 8.

He died of COVID-19 pneumonia on February 13,2020.

Liu Fan, 59

Nurse, injection room, service center, Liyuan Street Community Health Center, Wuchang Hospital, Wuhan

Liu Fan, 59

Nurse, injection room, service center, Liyuan Street Community Health Center, Wuchang Hospital, Wuhan

On February 15, the Wuchang Hospital in Wuhan announced that because of his age, Liu Fan had not been assigned to work in the front line of fever clinic, pre-examination and triage station, and has always been engaged in injection work in the community. It is reported that Liu fan in his life to apply for a deferred retirement.

Around 17:30 on February 14, Liu fan suffered cardiac arrest and died around 18:30 of ineffectual resuscitation.

Duan Zhengcheng, 86

Chinese Academy of Engineering, Professor, Huazhong University of Science and Technology, chief scientist, National Engineering Research Center for the digitization of manufacturing equipment, and expert in machine building and automation.

Duan Zhengcheng, 86

Chinese Academy of Engineering, Professor, Huazhong University of Science and Technology, chief scientist, National Engineering Research Center for the digitization of manufacturing equipment, and expert in machine building and automation.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In 1996, Duan Zhengcheng combined mechanical science with radiotherapy medicine to develop the first international whole body gamma knife. In 1999, Duan Zhengcheng developed the world's first large-scale radiotherapy equipment, called the total body gamma knife, which can rotate and focus the gamma rays on the tumor after precise positioning, thus killing the tumor cells, greatly reduce the damage to normal tissues and organs of human body. It has been used in more than 100 hospitals nationwide, benefiting nearly one million people.

Professor Duan Zhengcheng, who was diagnosed with COVID-19 pneumonia on January 29 and suffered from underlying diseases such as diabetes, died at 19:35 on February 15 in hospital after medical treatment failed.

On February 16, the autopsy of the first and second cases of NCP in China was completed in Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital, and NCP pathology was successfully obtained. The pathology of the new coronary pneumonia obtained by dissection is of great help to explore the clinical pathological changes and disease mechanism of the patients with the new coronary pneumonia, and to find out the pathogenicity and lethality of the new coronary pneumonia, to provide a basis for the future clinical treatment of critically ill patients.

We also pay tribute to the two donors and their families.
